Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.02,1:09:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that there is an energy field, that they are like Don Quixote, fighting their
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.90,1:09:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,own projections in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.06,1:09:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This is really their own negative viewpoints that they project on the world and they then
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.84,1:10:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,spend the rest of their life battling that which they have projected out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.35,1:10:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the comedy of it all, that's the basis of all humor, you know, laughing at those
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.09,1:10:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,qualities of life, holding them from a position which exposes the paradox.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.39,1:10:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because humor is seeing the paradox, the funniness of it, the humor of it, to hold lightly.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.92,1:10:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have to become at the effect then of anything out there whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.78,1:10:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's we ourselves who determine by our attitudes, by our position, whether life is experienced
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.42,1:10:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,as joyful and harmonious, easygoing, or whether we experience it as our enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.51,1:10:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to go with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.59,1:10:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Go with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.35,1:10:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin to admire people who are capable and easygoing.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.07,1:11:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the objection comes up, well, the easygoing person, aren't they a pushover,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.58,1:11:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, in business?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.86,1:11:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The misunderstanding of what easygoingness means.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.18,1:11:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No, easygoing means acceptance.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.16,1:11:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It means to be adequate.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.58,1:11:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can see the humor of life, if you feel adequate and solid within yourself, if you
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.88,1:11:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,realize that you're the source of how you experience life.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.14,1:11:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you can handle those things which the world considers difficult with ease.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.90,1:11:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be the boss, and if the janitor doesn't show up, it doesn't bother you at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.02,1:11:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When the business closes for the day, you take off your coat, roll up your sleeves, and
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.92,1:11:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you sweep it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.61,1:11:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't make any difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.11,1:11:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.11,1:11:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that which I am is unaffected by all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.76,1:11:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is that I am that which experiences experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.66,1:11:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The realization that I am the experiencer of experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.66,1:11:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That that's where I live.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.66,1:11:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I live within my consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.78,1:11:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't make any difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.10,1:11:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether I surround myself with appurtenances that look important, or whether I roll up
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.68,1:12:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,my sleeves and I sweep out the office myself, that which I am is totally unaffected.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.60,1:12:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That which I am is just enjoying the experience of its own existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.12,1:12:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Enjoying one's own inner aliveness.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.22,1:12:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Stress just doesn't exist in that kind of a position about the world, where we clearly
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.84,1:12:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,identify who we really are.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.60,1:12:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When we stop identifying with the body as being who we are, we pointed out right in the
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.78,1:12:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,very beginning, the body is half a dozen times removed from the reality of who we are.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.62,1:12:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When we stop identifying with the events out there, when we stop giving them power over
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.90,1:12:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,our life, then comes an inner serenity.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.80,1:12:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's like the solar plexus can relax at last.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.12,1:12:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We're out of danger.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.84,1:12:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We're out of danger.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.84,1:12:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We've sort of transcended the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.76,1:12:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We've learned what the source of stress is.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.32,1:13:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Just knowing what the source of stress is already makes us immune to it, already moves
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.74,1:13:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,us into a different way of being with life, allows us to see it as our own creation.
